dream: I love my partner a lot, and she loves me back. We care a lot about each other and have a very strong bond. I had a dream where she broke up with me and I can't remember over what it was. We don't have any reason to break up, and as far as I know, we never ever will.
interpretation: Dreams can often be a reflection of our fears and anxieties, even if they don't directly correspond to our reality. In this dream, the fear of your partner breaking up with you could stem from a subconscious worry about losing the relationship or a fear of the unknown. It is important to remember that dreams are not always literal and should not be interpreted as predictions of the future. Your strong bond and loving relationship with your partner in your waking life outweigh any concerns expressed in the dream. However, if the dream continues to cause you distress, it may be beneficial to communicate your feelings with your partner to strengthen your connection and alleviate any uncertainties in your relationship.
title: "Unraveling Bonds: The Dream of An Unexplained Breakup"

dream: So for preferance, I am currently in the process of reincarnation. I am reincarnating at a Korean boy named Mok Inoon (목인운) and will be reborn in Korea. Last night, I had a dream that I was in a phone store waiting in a line. While waiting, the person ahead of me was being helped and the employee helping them was talking to the person about "ideal life" and things of that nature. While I was waiting, I was talking on my phone to an ex-best friend, but it was a friendly chat like we were still friends. When I was called up, I changed the language on my phone from Korean to English, because I was embarassed that it was Korean. The employee helping me asked if my name was "Kim Won-seok" (김원석; Inoon's maternal great-grandfather), but I got embarassed and quietly said "No, my name is Chance Hewitt." The employee then said to me "psychosis episode impending". What could this dream mean?
interpretation:
This dream can be interpreted as a reflection of your thoughts and emotions related to your process of reincarnation and upcoming rebirth in Korea. The phone store represents a place of communication and connection, symbolizing your potential for building new relationships and integrating into the Korean culture.

The person ahead of you discussing the "ideal life" may represent your own desires and aspirations for the new life you are about to enter. It could indicate that you have certain expectations or dreams for how you want this reincarnation to unfold.

Talking to your ex-best friend on the phone signifies unresolved feelings or unfinished business with this person. The fact that the conversation was friendly suggests that you still hold positive emotions towards them, despite the past issues. This could be a subconscious reminder for you to address any unresolved issues or seek closure before starting this new phase of your life.

Changing the language on your phone from Korean to English may indicate a temporary discomfort or hesitation regarding fully embracing the Korean culture and language. It could symbolize a fear of being seen as "other" or feeling different from those around you.

The employee's question about your name may highlight a conflict between your past and future identities. While the employee suggests a connection to your past life's lineage, you respond with a different name, "Chance Hewitt," which may represent a desire for a fresh start and individuality in your new life.

The employee's statement, "psychosis episode impending," can be seen as a symbolic warning or reminder from your subconscious. It may suggest that there is a need for you to maintain a balance between your past and future selves, ensuring that you stay grounded and mentally healthy during this process of reincarnation.

Overall, this dream suggests a mixture of excitement and apprehension as you embark on this new chapter of your life. It encourages you to address any unresolved issues from your past and find a healthy balance between embracing the new culture while staying true to your authentic self.
title: "The Line of Rebirth: Embracing Change and Identity in a Phone Store Dream"

Overall, this dream may suggest that you are encountering or anticipating some form of distress or chaos in your waking life, and you are seeking ways to escape or protect yourself from it. It might be helpful to explore the source of these fears or anxieties in order to address and resolve them.
title: Cafe Chaos: Terrifying Screams, Zombie Encounter, and a Desperate Dash into the Dark Forest

dream:
I’ve entered some type of maze 
Ria and Michael and some other people go in 

We’re told to navigate the maze we should use our spirit guides and intuition 
Not to panic 

And we say at least we’re together we can figure it out together 

Suddenly I become separated from the group I call Michael for advice where to go 
He says his guides are telling him to follow the arrows 
Reminds me that if we get lost someone will eventually come and find us 

I walk through a corridor , Michael tells me to go through a specific door 
I do 
Feels like I may be on the right track
Then my phone disappears / stops working

I wander a while coming to dead ends 
Then 
I find another door 
I open it and inside is a room filled with lots of large snoozing lions on a very long winding staircases 
There’s a door at the end

My first thought is that it’s too dangerous and it must be a trick door 
But I start getting nervous about getting lost and proceed down the room skipping the lions 
They. Wake up and lunge after me 
I realize that this room was a trick 
The door at the end was painted on 

I backtrack pushing various bits of stone onto the lions and push lions out of the way ( they fall over like styrofoam, dream lions are lightweight )
The whole staircase crumbles with the lions and I scramble back up to the top and go back through the door I came through to continue the maze
interpretation:
This dream seems to symbolize a journey or challenge in your waking life, where you and some people (represented by Ria, Michael, and others) are trying to navigate through a maze. The maze represents obstacles or complexities you are facing. The advice to use your spirit guides and intuition suggests that you should trust your inner wisdom to guide you through this situation and avoid panicking.

The separation from the group may indicate a feeling of being on your own or unsupported in this journey. Calling Michael for advice could symbolize seeking guidance or reassurance from someone you trust. His suggestion to follow the arrows represents following clear signs or indications that may lead you in the right direction. The disappearance or malfunctioning of your phone may symbolize a loss of communication or connection with others.

As you continue through the maze, you encounter dead ends, which could symbolize obstacles or challenges that impede your progress. However, finding another door represents finding an alternative path or solution. The room filled with snoozing lions on the winding staircase may represent a risky or dangerous situation that you are hesitant to face. Trusting your instincts, you proceed cautiously but trigger the lions to wake up and chase after you. This could suggest that taking bold actions or risks may have unexpected consequences.

Realizing that the lions and the painted door were a trick, and subsequently backtracking, demonstrates your resilience and ability to adapt. Pushing stones onto the lions and maneuvering around them represents finding creative solutions to overcome obstacles. The crumbling staircase and scrambling back to the top symbolize learning from your mistakes and returning to a previous point to continue your journey.

Overall, this dream suggests that you are navigating through a challenging situation in your waking life, and it encourages you to trust your instincts, seek guidance when needed, and be adaptable in finding solutions. It also reminds you to be cautious of potential traps or trickery along the way.
title: "Maze of Intuition: Lost Amidst Lions and Illusions"

dream:
The first part of my dream was me ordering food at a restaurant but there was some chaos and i didn't know where to order. When I get to the front of the line, I find out I have to call the online ordering service in order to place my order. I call the number and try to order what I want, but the lady on the phone says I cant because only certain cities can order that item. I try to tell her the item is on the menu where I am but just decide to order something else instead. I realize that I need to leave just to drive back for some reason unclear to me now. I get on my motorcycle and speed through streets trying to get back to the restaurant on time because it's about to close. As I'm driving another motorcycle is coming to the point on an adjacent road to the one I'm on. We start to race to the restaurant against each other. Upon arriving at the restaurant, we understand we are both trying to get to there before it closes. We run up the stairs to find the restaurant closed even those its 6 minutes before the actual close time. A group of people is outside and we bang on the door to get in. Luckily the manager let's us get in to get our food. Inside the restaurant there is a tiny cart where we get our food. After staying for a bit, I take a bag of a giant water jug and a smaller paper bag with a beer and a plastic cup. Somehow in gathering my belongings, I drop the can of beer and it starts leaking so I put it in the plastic cup to contain the beer. As I'm riding in a Tuk-tuk the beer keeps leaking but it's disappearing.

In the second part of the dream I'm at an airport. I'm at the gate of where I think I should be departing but realize the gate has been moved to a whole other airport. As I realize this I see another passenger realize the same. We get together and start running for the exit. We go to the elevators which is a small silver box with no buttons. The other woman disappears behind a small open door. The elevator is moving but then there is a weird spinning noise. A voice comes over a loudspeaker to say that the wheels are in spin mode and that we have to wait for help. I'm panicking because we are stuck and I'm claustrophobic and also because we are going to miss our flight. The elevator then free falls back down the ground floor. I black out but come to consciousness outside the elevator surrounded by others and the woman again, all unconscious on the floor. I wake her up and we deliriously run through the airport to get to the exit. However, the way I  thought we could go seems to keep leading us in the wrong direction and further into the airport. There are just more and more people and I can't figure out which way to go even though I know where the exit is in my mind. 

Then I woke up.
interpretation:
In the first part of your dream, the chaos and confusion at the restaurant represent feelings of uncertainty and indecision in your waking life. The difficulty in placing your order symbolizes a sense of frustration or obstacles in achieving what you desire. The restriction on ordering certain items in certain cities suggests limitations or restrictions in your current circumstances. The urgency to return to the restaurant before it closes may reflect a fear of missing out or a sense of time pressure in achieving your goals. The race against another person on a motorcycle represents competition or comparison with others in reaching your objectives.

Arriving at the closed restaurant highlights a concern about missed opportunities or feeling excluded. The need for the manager to let you in suggests a desire for second chances or someone in authority granting you access to what you desire. The tiny cart symbolizes your ability to adapt and make do with what is available to you. Dropping the can of beer and containing it in a plastic cup represents a need to manage or control a potentially enjoyable or pleasurable aspect of your life, but the fact that it keeps leaking and disappearing may indicate a difficulty in fully enjoying or savoring these experiences.

In the second part of your dream, being at the wrong gate at the airport signifies a sense of confusion or being off track in your current path or direction in life. The realization that the gate has been moved to another airport reflects a deviation or unexpected change in your plans or goals. The small silver elevator without buttons represents a lack of control or feeling trapped in a situation. The spinning noise and the announcement about the wheels in spin mode symbolize a loss of stability or unpredictability in your circumstances. The free fall of the elevator and blacking out suggests a loss of consciousness or feeling overwhelmed by the challenges you are facing.

The struggle to find the right way to the exit in the airport represents a sense of being lost or uncertain about the path forward. The increasing number of people and the confusion in finding the right direction indicate a sense of being overwhelmed or influenced by the opinions and actions of others, making it difficult for you to trust your own instincts or decisions.

Overall, this dream suggests that you may be experiencing uncertainty, frustration, and a lack of control in your waking life. It may be important for you to evaluate your goals, priorities, and the direction you are heading in order to regain a sense of clarity and confidence in pursuing what truly matters to you.
title: "Frantic Food Ordering, Chaotic Races, and Airport Escapades: A Dream of Confusion and Determination"
